    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And Mizpeh,.... Frequent mention is made of Mizpeh in Scripture; according to Fuller (t), it was about eight miles from Gibeah; it was near Ramathon, which Josephus says (u) was forty furlongs from Jerusalem: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Chephirah was one of the cities subject to Gibeon, Joshua 9:17. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and Chephirah was one of the cities subject to Gibeon, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 9:17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Mozah; there was a place called Motza, near to Jerusalem, where they used to go to get willows at the feast of tabernacles (w). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(t) Pisgah-Sight, B. 2. c. 12. p. 209. (u) Antiqu. l. 8. c. 12. sect. 3.((w) Misn. Succah, c. 4. sect. 5. ",
        "children": [
